        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:26PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 425 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Escobas, or 11 miles north of Bustamante, moving
southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oilton, Mirando City, and Bruni.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
